      "commit": {
        "parents": [
          {
            "commit": "a296e9433919a6d709ae7826ecc5310d9e2d1365",
            "subject": "LU-831 header: struct bit field should be unsigned type"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "niu@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2011-11-09 03:23:52.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Niu Yawei",
          "email": "niu@whamcloud.com",
          "date": "2011-11-16 05:00:07.000000000",
          "tz": -480
        },
        "subject": "LU-745 kernel: ost-pools test_23 hung",
        "message": "LU-745 kernel: ost-pools test_23 hung\n\nIt could be caused by a jbd2 bug which result in forever sleep\nin the do_get_write_access().\n\nhttp://www.spinics.net/lists/linux-ext4/msg24689.html\n\nIn do_get_write_access() we wait on BH_Unshadow bit for buffer to get\nfrom shadow state. The waking code in journal_commit_transaction() has\na bug because it does not issue a memory barrier after the buffer is moved\nfrom the shadow state and before wake_up_bit() is called. Thus a waitqueue\ncheck can happen before the buffer is actually moved from the shadow state\nand waiting process may never be woken. Fix the problem by issuing proper\nbarrier.\n\nSigned-off-by: Niu Yawei <niu@whamcloud.com>\nChange-Id: I44dce352babc6699cdacc00263bfd3f24538400c\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
